  "local_port": 55706,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is a good inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center near Fayette County IN?",
  "response": "When looking for a good inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center near Fayette County, Indiana, it's important to consider several factors such as the type of treatment offered, the facility's reputation, cost, and whether it accepts insurance. Here are a few reputable options within a reasonable distance from Fayette County:\n\n1. **Tara Treatment Center**\n   - **Location:** Franklin, IN (approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes from Fayette County)\n   - **Services:** Tara Treatment Center offers a comprehensive inpatient program for substance abuse treatment. They focus on individualized treatment plans and provide a range of therapeutic services including group therapy, individual counseling, and family therapy.\n   - **Website:** [Tara Treatment Center](https://www.taratreatment.com/)\n\n2. **Fairbanks**\n   - **Location:** Indianapolis, IN (approximately 1 hour and 30 minutes from Fayette County)\n   - **Services:** Fairbanks offers inpatient and residential treatment programs for substance abuse. They provide medically supervised detox, individual and group therapy, and aftercare planning.\n   - **Website:** [Fairbanks](https://www.fairbankscd.org/)\n\n3. **Richmond State Hospital**\n   - **Location:** Richmond, IN (approximately 30 minutes from Fayette County)\n   - **Services:** While primarily a psychiatric hospital, Richmond State Hospital also provides substance abuse treatment services, including inpatient care. They offer comprehensive assessments and treatment plans tailored to individual needs.\n   - **Website:** [Richmond State Hospital](https://www.in.gov/issa/rsh/)\n\n4. **Gallahue Mental Health Center**\n   - **Location:** Indianapolis, IN (approximately 1 hour and 30 minutes from Fayette County)\n   - **Services:** Part of Community Health Network, Gallahue offers inpatient substance abuse treatment with a focus on holistic care, including medical, psychological, and social support services.\n   - **Website:** [Gallahue Mental Health Center](https://www.ecommunity.com/services/behavioral-health/gallahue-mental-health-services)\n\nWhen choosing a rehab center, it's advisable to:\n- Verify whether the facility accepts your insurance or offers payment plans.\n- Contact the center directly to discuss your specific needs and inquire about the admission process.\n- Read reviews and possibly speak with former patients or their families to gauge the effectiveness of the treatment programs.\n\nSelecting the right rehab center is a crucial step in the recovery journey, and taking the time to research and choose wisely can make a significant difference.",
